text: The 1966 Cal State Los Angeles Diablos football team represented California State University, Los Angeles during the 1966 NCAA College Division football season. Cal State Los Angeles competed in the California Collegiate Athletic Association (CCAA). The team was led by first-year coach Jim Williams and played home games at the Rose Bowl in Pasadena, California.
